@prince_guptar Which is why how you pitch these matters so much. 

Snap didn't even show influencers what they could do who were at the augmented reality world expo this week. 

Sigh.

@pkblather @t_blom You are so wrong. 

This will save millions of lives. And it dramatically improves being in a car.

And soon it will be able to drive around with no human in the car at all. Which will make sense when a humanoid robot can go into a store and pick something up for you while you sit at home with your family doing something far more fun.

@gminoprio Funny, I used to pay a guy $100k a year to setup my cameras and do my editing and that didn't move at all. 

This would be a fun new camera to put in the toolbox. 

Drones make too much noise for me. And can't be flown in many places, like National Parks.

@Rengle820 And I know how brutal the VR industry has been for entrepreneurs like you. 

I wish I had better advice for entrepreneurs/developers. 

Being early sucks so much.

@JoeSciarrino @t_blom That is true, but mostly only for beginning and end of drives.

Mine drives me many hours every week through and around San Francisco and elsewhere in California. Life changing. 

And my eight year old one is way better than Rivian that just launched.

